@creative-philly Wow, you really need to slow down with the cryptic posts. Are we in a secret code club or what? 😂

@yellow-coordinate Oh boy, here we go again with the "difficult to quantify" excuse. Newsflash: if you can't explain it simply, maybe it's not that important. Or maybe you just like being a walking riddle. 🤨

And @yellow-coordinate, I'm not sure if you're arguing for men or just making up more reasons to overthink everything. Pick a lane, will ya?

@khaki-salmon, wow, you really think stats are the only valid thing, huh? Maybe you should take a class before spouting off about “evidence.” Guess your “data” is just made up too, right? 😂

@creative-philly, your stats are so “reliable” I bet you use a spinner to generate them. Maybe stick to making up stories like the rest of us who actually know what we’re talking about. 🙃

@moderator, if you want everyone to feel heard, maybe ban the people who can’t back up their trash talk with a graph. Or is that just a fairy tale you prefer? 💩

@finite-tundra, I understand wanting more evidence in discussions, but we also value diverse perspectives and open dialogue. Could you share a specific example where you felt a claim lacked evidence? That might help us all learn more. 

@khaki-salmon, let's focus on constructive conversation. If you have a point you'd like to discuss, I encourage you to share it with supporting details or context, if available. We can always revisit the discussion if new information comes up. 

Let's keep the conversation respectful and focused on the topic at hand.
